u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0TRUMP\u00a0\u00a0TRUTH\u00a0\u00a0", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2073952094030352628", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ATBlyYFSb", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 29, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8715339, "raw_content": "", "author": "KuzoKevin", "created": 1783307517635, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Maganifice7", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ATBlyYFSb.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/BillboardChris/status/2073952094030352628", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Life was simpler back when men wearing wigs and makeup and stuffing bras were just cross-dressers.  I can't believe we now tell kids they can identify as rabbits.", "last_comment_created": 1783311822132, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 29, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 33, "created": 1783303686000, "id": "2073952094030352628", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2073951710771564544/img/wUSfktA7MdeREV46.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2073951710771564544/pl/5N0lIxsSkpTGnrXf.m3u8?v=c97", "aspectRatio": [16, 9], "heightRatio": 56, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2073951710771564544/vid/avc1/480x270/OlxnUjYo86ruexK6.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1901861685000081408/D7iobPHe_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Billboard Chris \ud83c\udf0e", "username": "BillboardChris"}, "content": "I thought I\u2019d heard everything.\n\nThis woman in London would sew a fluffy tail on her son\u2019s bottom if he identified as a rabbit. \n\nOf course her reasoning is \u201cif it would prevent him from killing himself!\u201d\n\nIt\u2019s bunny-affirming care! \n\nMaybe England should do a trial on this after", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 557}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ATBlyYFWa", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 29, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8715340, "raw_content": "Warner Bros. Discovery faces significant financial challenges, heavily burdened by over $37 billion in long-term debt and ongoing struggles with declining viewership in traditional cable television. \n\n\nThe company has been dealing with major restructuring expenses, fluctuating box office returns, and has been navigating a complex process regarding a potential company split or sale.These financial hurdles are driven by specific factors:The Cable Decline: Like much of the traditional media industry, Warner Bros. Discovery is heavily reliant on linear TV (networks like CNN, TNT, and Discovery). \n\n\nThe shift toward streaming has caused sharp drops in both cable ad sales and affiliate revenue.Massive Debt Load: The debt originated from a series of massive corporate mergers, passing from Time Warner to AT&T, and finally to the Discovery merger. Servicing the interest on these billions is a major drain on company resources.Volatile Studio Returns: While the film and television studios (Warner Bros. Pictures and HBO) produce major hits, their performance can be inconsistent. \n\n\nFluctuating theater attendance and costly film budgets lead to volatile revenue swings.Restructuring and Write-downs: To manage costs and pay down debt, the company has frequently written off unreleased content, engaged in widespread workforce layoffs, and restructured operations, resulting in billions in one-time charges.", "author": "FlyinHeadlock", "created": 1783307546819, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "BlackJack1776", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Warner Bros. can't afford anymore Supergirl type flops. The company is heavily in debt.The original Supergirl was also bombed and bankrupted a couple of companies that tried to keep making Superman movies that failed.   ", "last_comment_created": 1783321816112, "content": "<p>Warner Bros. Discovery faces significant financial challenges, heavily burdened by over $37 billion in long-term debt and ongoing struggles with declining viewership in traditional cable television.</p>\n<p>The company has been dealing with major restructuring expenses, fluctuating box office returns, and has been navigating a complex process regarding a potential company split or sale.These financial hurdles are driven by specific factors:The Cable Decline: Like much of the traditional media industry, Warner Bros. Discovery is heavily reliant on linear TV (networks like CNN, TNT, and Discovery).</p>\n<p>The shift toward streaming has caused sharp drops in both cable ad sales and affiliate revenue.Massive Debt Load: The debt originated from a series of massive corporate mergers, passing from Time Warner to AT&amp;T, and finally to the Discovery merger. Servicing the interest on these billions is a major drain on company resources.Volatile Studio Returns: While the film and television studios (Warner Bros. Pictures and HBO) produce major hits, their performance can be inconsistent.</p>\n<p>Fluctua